  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    At the end of each sprint a sprint review meeting is held. During this meeting the Scrum team shows what they&#xD;
    accomplished during the sprint. Typically this takes the form of a demo of the new features.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    Participants in the sprint review typically include the Product Owner, the Scrum team, the ScrumMaster, management,&#xD;
    customers, and engineers from other projects.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    During the sprint review the project is assessed against the sprint goal determined during the Sprint planning meeting.&#xD;
    Ideally the team has completed each product backlog item brought into the sprint, but it is more important that they&#xD;
    achieve the overall goal of the sprint.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    在每一个Sprint结束时，召开Sprint评审会议。在会议上，Scrum团队演示在这个Sprint中他们的工作成果。典型的，采用对部分特性进行演示的形式。&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Sprint评审会议典型的参与者包括：产品负责人、Scrum团队成员、Scrum Master、管理者、客户，以及来自其他项目的工程师。&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
在Sprint评审会议上，依据在Sprint计划会议上制定的Sprint目标对项目进行评估。显然，团队应该已经完成在该Sprint中选定的产品Backlog中的条目，但更重要的是，达到了该Srint的目标。&lt;br /></mainDescription>
  <keyConsiderations>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The sprint review meeting is intentionally kept very informal, typically with rules forbidding the use of PowerPoint&#xD;
    slides and allowing no more than two hours of preparation time for the meeting. A sprint review meeting should not&#xD;
    become a distraction or significant detour for the team; rather, it should be a natural result of the sprint.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Sprint评审会议被有意的要求非正式，通常有规定禁止使用PowerPoint胶片并且时间不允许超过2个小时。Sprint评审会议对团队来说，不应该成为一个重要的或消遣弯道，而应该是一个Sprint的自然结果。&#xD;
&lt;/p></keyConsiderations>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
